Vice President Joe Biden and his wife Jill expressed their deep sadness over the Amtrak train derailment in Philadelphia. They thanked the first responders and others who have been helping those affected by the accident. Biden, who frequently travels on Amtrak, considered the company a second family and expressed his sympathy for the victims and their families. He emphasized that the victims could have been anyone's parents, children, or members of their communities. The Vice President concluded by saying that as a nation, they pray for the victims and their families.